huntYears.SEASON_DATE_TEXT: During open seasons on any 2022 Cache Antlerless Elk hunt - See the 2022 Antlerless Guidebook for details
huntYears.NOTES:
Hunters who obtain a Cache Antlerless Elk Conservation permit can hunt the following areas/seasons:
Cache, Richmond-Hyde Park: Aug 1 - Aug 19, 2022 and Oct 8 - Oct 30, 2022 and Nov 12, 2022 - Jan 15, 2023
Cache, East: Oct 8 - Oct 30, 2022
Cache, Rich: Oct 8 - Oct 30, 2022 and Nov 12, 2022 - Jan 15, 2023
Cache, Richards Hollow: Nov 12, 2022 - Jan 15, 2023

huntMaster.SPECIAL_INSTRUCTIONS: Any open antlerless elk units in the guidebook that include "Cache" in the unit name
huntMaster.SPECIAL_PROVISIONS: Cache antlerless elk conservation permits for the 2022-2024 permit cycle may be obtained through Rocky Mountain Elk Foundation, Safari Club International and Sportsman for Fish & Wildlife
huntMaster.NOTES:
Baiting big game for the purposes of hunting is now illegal in Utah.
Click here for more information.

The use of all trail cameras (including both non-handheld transmitting and non-transmitting devices) in the harvest or to aid in the harvest of big game is prohibited between July 31 and Dec. 31. Click here for more information.
huntMaster.HARVEST_REPORTING: Voluntary: Hunters who obtain this permit are encouraged, but not required, to submit a harvest report. Report your harvest online or by calling 1-800-221-0659.

huntBoundaryInfos.WMA_IN_UNIT: Millville Face, Hardware Ranch, Richmond, Providence, Coldwater
huntBoundaryInfos.CAMPGRND_INFO: Many primative campgrounds are available throughout the unit.  The Forest Service runs and maintains all fee areas, contact them for info.
huntBoundaryInfos.ATV_VEH_ACCESS: Travel maps and restrictions are available from the Forest Service. http://www.fs.usda.gov/main/uwcnf/
huntBoundaryInfos.BOUNDARY_DESCRIPTION:
Box Elder, Cache, Rich and Weber counties--Boundary begins at I-15 and the Utah-Idaho state line; east on this state line to the Utah-Wyoming state line; south on this state line to SR-16; northwest on SR-16 to SR-39; west on SR-39 to USFS Road 054 (Ant Flat Road); north on this road to Hardware Ranch and SR-101; west on SR-101 to USFS Road 245 (Left Hand Fork); northeast on this road to USFS Road 047; north on this road to USFS Road 081; northwest on this road to US-89; west on US-89 to Logan and US-89/91; south on US-89/91 to SR-165; south on SR-165 to SR-101; west on SR-101 to US-89/91; southwest on US-89/91 to Brigham City and  US-91; west on US-91 to I-15; north on I-15 to the Utah-Idaho state line.   Excludes all CWMUs. USGS 1:100,000 Maps: Logan, Ogden, Promontory Point, Tremonton. Boundary questions? 
Call Ogden office, 801-476-2740.

huntBoundaryInfos.CAMPGRND_INFO: Check with USFS and BLM for camping regulations and availability.
huntBoundaryInfos.SUGGESTED_MAPS:
Interactive maps are available at the Division's Website

http://wildlife.utah.gov/hunting-in-utah/hunt-boundary-maps.html
huntBoundaryInfos.ATV_VEH_ACCESS: Travel plans and regulations are available from the USFS and BLM
huntBoundaryInfos.PRIV_TRIBE_LAND_ISSUES: This unit is compised of mostly private land.  Be sure to get written permission to access private land for hunting.
huntBoundaryInfos.BOUNDARY_DESCRIPTION: Rich County--Boundary begins at the Utah-Wyoming state line and SR-16; northwest on SR-16 to SR-39; west on SR-39 to the Rich-Cache county line; north on this county line to the Utah-Idaho state line; east on this state line to the Utah-Wyoming state line; south on this state line to SR-16. Excludes all CWMUs. USGS 1:100,000 Maps: Logan, Ogden. Boundary questions? Call Ogden office, 801-476-2740.

huntBoundaryInfos.CAMPGRND_INFO: All campgrounds are primative within the unit.  Improved campgrounds will be closed for the season.
huntBoundaryInfos.SUGGESTED_MAPS: USFS Administrative Map for Logan Ranger District
huntBoundaryInfos.ATV_VEH_ACCESS: Motorized travel within the unit is closed by the Forest Service Nov. 15 annually to protect roads.
huntBoundaryInfos.BOUNDARY_DESCRIPTION: Cache County--Boundary begins SR-165 and SR-101 in Hyrum; east on SR-101 to USFS Road 245 (Left Hand fork); northeast on this road to USFS Road 047 (Herd Hollow);  north on this road to USFS Road 081 (Right Hand Fork); northwest on this road to US-89; west on US-89 to US-89/91; south on US-89/91 to SR-165; south on SR-165 to SR-101.  Excludes all CWMUs. USGS 1:100,000 Maps: Logan. Boundary questions? Call Ogden office, 801-476-2740.

huntBoundaryInfos.LAND_OWNERSHIP: Land is mostly private with some public wilderness areas on the east side of the unit.
huntBoundaryInfos.CAMPGRND_INFO: Camping is limited to undesignated areas on the wilderness area, and Smithfield Canyon prior to November 15 each year.  After November 15, campgrounds and roads will be closed by the Forest Service to prevent road damage.
huntBoundaryInfos.COUNTY_ROAD_INFO: Road access is limited.  Most access will be by foot or horse through the Richmond WMA property, walk in access properties, and from High Creek and Smithfield Canyons.
huntBoundaryInfos.PRIV_TRIBE_LAND_ISSUES: Mostly private land below the Forest Service boundary on the east side of the unit.
huntBoundaryInfos.BOUNDARY_DESCRIPTION: Box Elder and Cache counties--Boundary begins at the Utah-Idaho state line and I-15; south on I-15 to US-91; east and north on US-91 to 400 north and US-89 in Logan City; northeast on US-89 to Wood Camp Hollow drainage; northwest along this drainage to the Logan-Bear River drainage divide and USFS Trail 049; west on this trail to USFS Trail 005; north on this trail to the drainage divide between the Logan River and the Bear River in Cache Valley; north along this divide to the Utah-Idaho state line; west on this state line to I-15. Excludes all CWMUs. USGS 1:100,000 Maps: Logan, Promontory Point, Tremonton. Boundary questions? Call Ogden office, 801-476-2740.
